quran[52]{c,v,t}:
  69,1,The Inevitable Calamity
  69,2,What is the Inevitable Calamity
  69,3,And what shall make thee know that which the Inevitable Calamity is
  69,4,The tribes of Thamud and 'Aad belied the Striking Day
  69,5,"As for Thamud, they were destroyed by the outburst"
  69,6,"And as for 'Aad they were destroyed by a wind, furious. roaring"
  69,7,"To which He subjected them for seven nights and eight days in succession, so that thou mightest have seen men during it lying prostrate, as though they were stumps of palms ruined"
  69,8,Beholdest thou any of them remaining
  69,9,And Fir'awn and those before him and the overturned cities committed sin
  69,10,"And they disobeyed their Lord's apostle, so He laid hold of them with a grip increasing"
  69,11,"Verily We! when the water rose, We bare you upon the traversing ark"
  69,12,"That We might make it Unto you an admonition, and thot it might be retained by the retaining ears"
  69,13,And when the Trumpet shall sound a single blast
  69,14,And the earth and the mountains shall be borne and the twain shall be crushed with a single crash
  69,15,Then on that Day shall happen the Event
  69,16,"And the heaven shall be rent in sunder, it on that Day shall be frail"
  69,17,And the angels shall be on the borders thereof; and on that Day eight shall bear over them the Throne of thy Lord
  69,18,The Day whereon ye shall be mustered nothing hidden by you shall be hidden
  69,19,"Then as to him who will be vouchsafed his book in his right hand, he shall say: here! read my book"
  69,20,Verily I was sure that I should be a meeter of my reckoning
  69,21,Then he shall be in a life well-pleasing
  69,22,In a Garden lofty
  69,23,Clusters whereof shall be near at hand
  69,24,Eat and drink with benefit for that which ye sent on beforehand in dayspast
  69,25,"Then as to him who shall be vouchsafed his book in his left hand, he shall say: Oh! would that I had not been vouchsafed my book"
  69,26,Nor known whatever was my reckoning
  69,27,"Oh, would that it had been the ending"
  69,28,"My riches have: availed me not"
  69,29,There hath perished from me my authority
  69,30,Lay hold of him and chain him
  69,31,Then in the Scorch roast him
  69,32,"Then, in a chain whereof the length is seventy Cubits, bind him"
  69,33,"Verily he was wont not to believe in Allah, the Mighty"
  69,34,Nor he urged on others the feeding of the poor
  69,35,Wherefore for him here this Day there is no friend
  69,36,Nor any food save filthy corruption
  69,37,None shall eat it but the sinners
  69,38,I swear by that which ye see
  69,39,And that which ye see not
  69,40,That it is surely the speech brought by messenger honourable
  69,41,And it is not the speech of a poet. Little it is that ye believe
  69,42,Nor is it the speech of a sooth- sayer. Little are ye admonished
  69,43,It is a Revelation from the Lord of the worlds
  69,44,And if he had forged concerning us some discourses
  69,45,We surely had lain hold of him by the right hand
  69,46,And then severed his life-vein
  69,47,And not one of you would have withheld us from punishing him
  69,48,And verily it is an Admonition Unto the God-fearing
  69,49,And verily We! We know that some among you are beliers thereof
  69,50,And verily it shall be an occasion of anguish Unto the infidels
  69,51,And verily it is the truth of assured certainty
  69,52,"Wherefore hallow thou the name of thy Lord, the Mighty"